# Use .claude Resources

Use the agents, skills, and context from `.claude/` and `.cursor/`. Delegate via the Task tool with the correct `subagent_type`. Read skills and context when working in relevant domains.

## Agents — Delegate via Task Tool

| Subagent Type | When to Use |
|----------------|-------------|
| `master-orchestrator-agent` | Feature spans backend + frontend + contracts; coordinate multi-agent plan |
| `backend-core-agent` | DB schema, RLS, Edge Functions, anti-cheat, leaderboard, entitlements, Supabase |
| `frontend-core-agent` | Expo/React Native UI, Zustand, navigation, API integration, grid performance, offline |
| `contract-guardian` | After API/schema changes; validate CONTRACTS/ sync |
| `monetization-agent` | IAP, RevenueCat, AdMob, paywalls, entitlement UI |
| `performance-agent` | React Native render optimization, memoization, component splitting |
| `release-agent` | Build prep, EAS builds, changelogs, store metadata |
| `code-review` | User asks for code review; before merge; git diff or specific files |
| `design-review` | User asks for design audit; UI/UX review; use Playwright on admin |
| `security-review` | Before merging backend/API changes; OWASP scan on git diff |

